00:00:07.642 --> 00:00:10.010 position:21% line:89% align:start
(intense rock music)

00:00:16.885 --> 00:00:18.318 position:27% line:83% align:start
All right, listen
up, you grunts!

00:00:18.352 --> 00:00:21.890 position:21% line:83% align:start
Toman's new captain
of the third division

00:00:21.923 --> 00:00:25.058 position:16% line:83% align:start
is sitting here right
behind me: Tetta Kisaki!

00:00:26.059 --> 00:00:28.696 position:24% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi inhales)

00:00:28.730 --> 00:00:31.799 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(blow thumps)
-(Kisaki grunts)

00:00:31.833 --> 00:00:34.502 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hey, so what's goin' on here?

00:00:34.536 --> 00:00:35.503 position:35% line:89% align:start
[All] Huh?

00:00:35.537 --> 00:00:38.940 position:16% line:83% align:start
Looks like I nearly
missed the fun! (grunts)

00:00:38.973 --> 00:00:41.108 position:21% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi grunting)

00:00:41.141 --> 00:00:43.076 position:30% line:89% align:start
(Baji snickers)

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:44.946 position:19% line:89% align:start
Why are you here, Baji?

00:00:44.979 --> 00:00:46.014 position:19% line:89% align:start
You've been banned from

00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:48.248 position:24% line:83% align:start
attending our
meetings, remember?

00:00:48.282 --> 00:00:52.252 position:13% line:83% align:start
So what, does that mean
I'm finally gonna be fired?

00:00:52.286 --> 00:00:54.087 position:27% line:83% align:start
For ruining your
precious meeting?

00:00:54.121 --> 00:00:57.124 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] What the hell
is this guy talking about?

00:00:58.593 --> 00:01:01.596 position:10% line:83% align:start
You don't want any
troublemakers, do you, Mikey?

00:01:02.496 --> 00:01:03.497 position:44% line:89% align:start
Baji!

00:01:04.832 --> 00:01:07.067 position:7% line:89% align:start
So your first division captain

00:01:07.100 --> 00:01:09.202 position:7% line:89% align:start
will just go ahead and resign.

00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:11.071 position:19% line:89% align:start
And starting right now,

00:01:11.104 --> 00:01:13.575 position:19% line:83% align:start
Toman's former captain
becomes its enemy.

00:01:17.579 --> 00:01:18.746 position:27% line:89% align:start
I need something.

00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:19.747 position:38% line:89% align:start
A favor.

00:01:19.781 --> 00:01:22.951 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, sure.

00:01:22.984 --> 00:01:25.085 position:16% line:83% align:start
I want you to bring
Baji back from Valhalla.

00:01:26.588 --> 00:01:27.622 position:19% line:89% align:start
Think you can do that?

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:30.024 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:01:30.058 --> 00:01:32.527 position:16% line:83% align:start
If that's what you
want, Mikey, you got it!

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:37.464 position:10% line:83% align:start
But, uh, do you think I could
ask for one thing in return?

00:01:39.366 --> 00:01:43.303 position:21% line:83% align:start
You've gotta kick
Kisaki out of Toman.

00:01:44.572 --> 00:01:45.372 position:44% line:89% align:start
Fine.

00:01:46.273 --> 00:01:47.942 position:24% line:83% align:start
We're going to end
up butting heads

00:01:47.976 --> 00:01:49.978 position:13% line:89% align:start
with Valhalla pretty soon.

00:01:50.011 --> 00:01:52.145 position:27% line:83% align:start
Just bring Baji
back before then.

00:01:52.179 --> 00:01:54.882 position:13% line:83% align:start
Prove you can be even more
useful to me than Kisaki.

00:01:56.517 --> 00:01:59.152 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gulps)

00:02:04.224 --> 00:02:09.162 position:21% line:83% align:start
-(traffic whooshing)
-(footsteps thumping)

00:02:22.677 --> 00:02:24.846 position:30% line:89% align:start
(school chimes)

00:02:35.288 --> 00:02:40.061 position:27% line:83% align:start
-(student laughs)
-(cheerful music)

00:02:40.094 --> 00:02:41.729 position:24% line:89% align:start
(students giggling)

00:02:41.763 --> 00:02:43.296 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, girls, slow down!

00:02:45.867 --> 00:02:46.834 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah, that's right.

00:02:46.868 --> 00:02:49.302 position:13% line:89% align:start
I couldn't even believe it.

00:02:50.872 --> 00:02:53.708 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi sighs)

00:02:57.210 --> 00:03:00.081 position:16% line:83% align:start
I want you to bring
Baji back from Valhalla.

00:03:00.114 --> 00:03:02.182 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(Takemichi gulps)
-But if you fail,

00:03:02.215 --> 00:03:04.052 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'll kill you.

00:03:04.085 --> 00:03:06.821 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] (exhales)
What am I gonna do?

00:03:06.854 --> 00:03:07.855 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Akkun] Takemichi!

00:03:07.889 --> 00:03:09.023 position:38% line:89% align:start
Now what?

00:03:09.057 --> 00:03:10.525 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, we heard the news!

00:03:10.558 --> 00:03:13.561 position:10% line:83% align:start
So I guess you're officially
part of Toman now, huh?

00:03:13.594 --> 00:03:14.394 position:33% line:89% align:start
Yeah, well...

00:03:18.766 --> 00:03:20.134 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hey, what's the matter?

00:03:20.168 --> 00:03:21.636 position:24% line:89% align:start
Why so bummed out?

00:03:21.669 --> 00:03:22.637 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:03:22.670 --> 00:03:23.838 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:03:23.871 --> 00:03:25.540 position:10% line:89% align:start
Ah, it's nothing. (chuckles)

00:03:25.573 --> 00:03:27.642 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm not really sure
how it happened.

00:03:27.675 --> 00:03:28.876 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's kinda weird.

00:03:28.910 --> 00:03:30.978 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hey, tell us all about it!

00:03:31.012 --> 00:03:34.515 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] Ah, I can't
even look Akkun in the eye!

00:03:35.850 --> 00:03:38.418 position:24% line:83% align:start
I can't believe our
Crybaby is in Toman.

00:03:38.452 --> 00:03:40.888 position:19% line:83% align:start
Man, if you're in, then
I wanna join up, too.

00:03:40.922 --> 00:03:42.557 position:24% line:89% align:start
(sighs) Yeah, well,

00:03:42.590 --> 00:03:45.492 position:16% line:83% align:start
it's really not as great
as you guys are thinking.

00:03:45.526 --> 00:03:46.894 position:35% line:89% align:start
[All] Huh?

00:03:46.928 --> 00:03:47.929 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:03:50.497 --> 00:03:55.503 position:5% line:83% align:start
-(vocalist singing in Japanese)
-(opening theme music)

00:05:22.690 --> 00:05:23.490 position:38% line:5% align:start
I get it.

00:05:24.659 --> 00:05:27.195 position:13% line:5% align:start
So if you don't get former
first division captain Baji

00:05:27.228 --> 00:05:29.764 position:19% line:5% align:start
to switch from
Valhalla back to Toman,

00:05:29.797 --> 00:05:32.266 position:24% line:83% align:start
then Mikey told you
he's gonna kill you.

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:33.433 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Yeah.

00:05:33.466 --> 00:05:35.169 position:21% line:83% align:start
And I only have until
Toman's showdown

00:05:35.203 --> 00:05:36.838 position:7% line:89% align:start
with Valhalla starts to do it.

00:05:36.871 --> 00:05:39.907 position:13% line:83% align:start
And who the hell even knows
when that might happen?

00:05:39.941 --> 00:05:41.108 position:30% line:89% align:start
If it's today-

00:05:41.142 --> 00:05:43.077 position:21% line:83% align:start
(gasps) Then I guess
this is goodbye.

00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:44.846 position:10% line:89% align:start
But we'll all mourn for you.

00:05:44.879 --> 00:05:46.080 position:30% line:89% align:start
Not to mention,

00:05:46.113 --> 00:05:47.248 position:16% line:89% align:start
I have no way of knowing

00:05:47.281 --> 00:05:49.584 position:19% line:83% align:start
what's going on
internally with Toman.

00:05:49.617 --> 00:05:52.787 position:13% line:83% align:start
And I barely even know
what this Valhalla gang is.

00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:54.722 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hey, Gang-o-pedia.

00:05:54.755 --> 00:05:55.857 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:55.890 --> 00:05:57.692 position:24% line:89% align:start
Okay, I'll explain.

00:05:57.725 --> 00:05:59.426 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'll try to use small words.

00:06:00.628 --> 00:06:01.929 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(chalk scratching)
-(mysterious music)

00:06:01.963 --> 00:06:05.199 position:16% line:83% align:start
The Tokyo Mangi Gang,
or just Toman for short.

00:06:05.233 --> 00:06:06.834 position:27% line:83% align:start
The commander, of
course, is Mikey,

00:06:06.868 --> 00:06:08.636 position:21% line:83% align:start
and the vice
commander is Draken.

00:06:08.669 --> 00:06:10.370 position:10% line:89% align:start
Under them are five divisions

00:06:10.403 --> 00:06:12.540 position:21% line:83% align:start
with about 20 members
in each division,

00:06:12.573 --> 00:06:15.009 position:27% line:83% align:start
which makes Toman
a huge biker gang

00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:17.712 position:7% line:89% align:start
with about 100 active members.

00:06:17.745 --> 00:06:19.881 position:24% line:83% align:start
Everyone following
all this so far?

00:06:19.914 --> 00:06:22.149 position:21% line:89% align:start
Whoa, I had no idea.

00:06:22.183 --> 00:06:23.317 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you kidding me?

00:06:23.351 --> 00:06:25.485 position:21% line:83% align:start
And you call yourself
a delinquent?!

00:06:25.519 --> 00:06:26.554 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Sorry.

00:06:26.587 --> 00:06:28.155 position:24% line:83% align:start
You'd better start
taking some notes.

00:06:28.189 --> 00:06:30.057 position:27% line:83% align:start
This is all gonna
be on the test.

00:06:30.091 --> 00:06:31.092 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(boys snickering)
-Huh?

00:06:31.125 --> 00:06:32.894 position:10% line:89% align:start
You three, quit goofing off!

00:06:32.927 --> 00:06:35.696 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] (snickers) Talk
about overplaying the part.

00:06:35.730 --> 00:06:37.464 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kazushi] From what
I had heard recently,

00:06:37.497 --> 00:06:39.166 position:19% line:83% align:start
the former third
division captain, Pah,

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.269 position:13% line:89% align:start
was arrested by the police,

00:06:41.302 --> 00:06:43.170 position:27% line:83% align:start
and so his former
vice captain, Peh,

00:06:43.204 --> 00:06:45.139 position:27% line:83% align:start
was moved to the
second division.

00:06:45.172 --> 00:06:46.140 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:46.173 --> 00:06:47.440 position:24% line:89% align:start
I didn't know that!

00:06:47.474 --> 00:06:49.409 position:19% line:83% align:start
So they put Peh in the
division under Mitsuya?

00:06:49.442 --> 00:06:50.845 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kazushi] Yes.

00:06:50.878 --> 00:06:52.747 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] That means I'm in
the same division with Peh!

00:06:52.780 --> 00:06:54.782 position:19% line:83% align:start
That guy's had it in
for me from the start!

00:06:54.815 --> 00:06:55.783 position:35% line:89% align:start
Takemitchy!

00:06:55.816 --> 00:06:57.585 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] Even
his voice is scary.

00:06:57.618 --> 00:07:01.421 position:7% line:83% align:start
And the one who took his place
as third division captain?

00:07:01.454 --> 00:07:03.824 position:27% line:89% align:start
(grunts) Kisaki.

00:07:03.858 --> 00:07:05.026 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:07:05.059 --> 00:07:06.627 position:16% line:89% align:start
Former leader of Moebius.

00:07:06.661 --> 00:07:08.296 position:7% line:89% align:start
Moebius was a fractured entity

00:07:08.329 --> 00:07:10.398 position:21% line:83% align:start
right from the start
of its existence.

00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:13.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
One half was born in
1988 and led by Osanai

00:07:13.267 --> 00:07:15.536 position:5% line:89% align:start
and the other in 1990 by Kisaki,

00:07:15.569 --> 00:07:17.405 position:21% line:83% align:start
and they were always
butting heads.

00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:18.506 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Atsushi] Hmm.

00:07:18.539 --> 00:07:20.440 position:24% line:83% align:start
So even though they
were all one gang,

00:07:20.473 --> 00:07:22.143 position:24% line:83% align:start
there was a lot of
internal conflict.

00:07:22.176 --> 00:07:24.278 position:27% line:83% align:start
After Osanai got
beaten by Mikey,

00:07:24.312 --> 00:07:26.747 position:5% line:89% align:start
Moebius was basically disbanded.

00:07:26.781 --> 00:07:30.483 position:13% line:83% align:start
And then the 1990 group
led by Kisaki joined Toman,

00:07:30.518 --> 00:07:32.452 position:19% line:83% align:start
which resulted in
Toman growing instantly

00:07:32.485 --> 00:07:35.423 position:16% line:89% align:start
from 100 members to 150.

00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:37.591 position:5% line:89% align:start
It also meant that within Toman,

00:07:37.625 --> 00:07:39.994 position:19% line:83% align:start
Kisaki's third division
ended up way bigger

00:07:40.027 --> 00:07:41.295 position:16% line:89% align:start
than any other division.

00:07:41.329 --> 00:07:43.463 position:24% line:83% align:start
Kisaki's bad news,
but he's strong.

00:07:43.496 --> 00:07:46.367 position:16% line:83% align:start
And in the future, we'll
need that strength.

00:07:46.400 --> 00:07:47.868 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi huffs)

00:07:47.902 --> 00:07:50.237 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Takuya] Then what happened
to the Moebius members

00:07:50.271 --> 00:07:51.973 position:7% line:89% align:start
that were followers of Osanai?

00:07:52.006 --> 00:07:54.675 position:13% line:83% align:start
The remaining members
from the '88 and '90 gangs

00:07:54.709 --> 00:07:58.245 position:7% line:83% align:start
joined together under a
different leader: Shuji Hanma.

00:07:59.413 --> 00:08:00.614 position:44% line:89% align:start
Him?!

00:08:02.083 --> 00:08:04.318 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gasps) That's right.

00:08:04.352 --> 00:08:06.053 position:10% line:89% align:start
At the battle on August 3rd,

00:08:06.087 --> 00:08:08.488 position:19% line:83% align:start
he said he was just the
temporary commander.

00:08:08.522 --> 00:08:11.459 position:16% line:83% align:start
So then Hanma took those
remaining Moebius members

00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.493 position:16% line:83% align:start
and joined them with all
the anti-Toman forces

00:08:13.527 --> 00:08:15.997 position:24% line:89% align:start
to create Valhalla.

00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:19.333 position:13% line:83% align:start
Valhalla's sitting at about
300 members right now.

00:08:19.367 --> 00:08:20.868 position:13% line:89% align:start
You've gotta be kidding me!

00:08:22.003 --> 00:08:24.605 position:24% line:83% align:start
That freak is
commanding 300 men?

00:08:24.638 --> 00:08:28.509 position:19% line:83% align:start
(tuts) He's the acting
commander, remember.

00:08:28.542 --> 00:08:31.278 position:19% line:83% align:start
No one knows yet who
the real commander is.

00:08:31.312 --> 00:08:34.148 position:13% line:89% align:start
The commander has no face.

00:08:34.181 --> 00:08:36.183 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's why they call Valhalla

00:08:36.217 --> 00:08:37.718 position:24% line:89% align:start
The Headless Angel.

00:08:39.186 --> 00:08:42.189 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] So that's
the gang Baji's with now.

00:08:42.223 --> 00:08:44.859 position:16% line:83% align:start
I guess I'm gonna have to
meet with him in person

00:08:44.892 --> 00:08:47.561 position:13% line:83% align:start
and then try to convince
him to come back to Toman.

00:08:48.329 --> 00:08:49.530 position:38% line:89% align:start
But how?

00:08:52.666 --> 00:08:54.168 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Hey, there.
-Huh?

00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:56.070 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Kazutora] I'm looking
for a second-year kid

00:08:56.103 --> 00:08:57.071 position:30% line:89% align:start
named Hanagaki.

00:08:57.104 --> 00:08:59.140 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Uh...
-He's in Class 3.

00:08:59.173 --> 00:09:00.374 position:38% line:89% align:start
Ah, cool.

00:09:00.408 --> 00:09:01.609 position:27% line:89% align:start
Okay, thank you.

00:09:03.878 --> 00:09:06.580 position:35% line:89% align:start
(both sigh)

00:09:06.614 --> 00:09:09.083 position:16% line:83% align:start
Since when is there a guy
that hot at our school?

00:09:09.116 --> 00:09:11.952 position:16% line:83% align:start
With shoes like those,
he must be a third-year.

00:09:11.986 --> 00:09:13.587 position:24% line:83% align:start
The former Moebius
members are led

00:09:13.621 --> 00:09:16.457 position:21% line:83% align:start
by Valhalla's Number
Two, Shuji Hanma,

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:18.292 position:27% line:83% align:start
while the other
anti-Toman forces

00:09:18.325 --> 00:09:19.427 position:13% line:89% align:start
gather under the leadership

00:09:19.460 --> 00:09:23.597 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(chalk scratching)
-(Takemichi sighs)

00:09:23.631 --> 00:09:26.600 position:19% line:83% align:start
of their Number Three,
Kazutora Hanemiya.

00:09:26.634 --> 00:09:28.102 position:30% line:89% align:start
(door rattles)

00:09:28.135 --> 00:09:29.103 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:09:29.136 --> 00:09:30.104 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Both] Huh?

00:09:30.137 --> 00:09:31.138 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Both] Huh?

00:09:35.009 --> 00:09:35.810 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hi, there.

00:09:46.420 --> 00:09:47.588 position:21% line:89% align:start
Did I get here late?

00:09:47.621 --> 00:09:49.757 position:16% line:89% align:start
Are classes over already?

00:09:49.790 --> 00:09:51.425 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Makoto] Who the hell are you?

00:09:51.459 --> 00:09:52.927 position:24% line:83% align:start
I've never seen you
around here before.

00:09:52.960 --> 00:09:55.096 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, that's not a very
polite thing to say!

00:09:55.129 --> 00:09:57.264 position:19% line:83% align:start
No respect for an
upperclassman, I guess.

00:09:57.298 --> 00:09:59.300 position:5% line:89% align:start
Huh? What are you talking about?

00:09:59.333 --> 00:10:00.968 position:13% line:89% align:start
I've never seen you before.

00:10:01.001 --> 00:10:04.205 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, uh, uh-oh.

00:10:04.238 --> 00:10:05.239 position:47% line:89% align:start
Uh.

00:10:07.074 --> 00:10:09.477 position:19% line:83% align:start
Watch what the hell
you're saying, Makoto!

00:10:09.511 --> 00:10:11.546 position:24% line:83% align:start
He's got a tiger
tattoo on his neck!

00:10:11.580 --> 00:10:13.214 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah? So what?

00:10:13.247 --> 00:10:16.917 position:16% line:83% align:start
Anyway, do you guys
know Takemichi Hanagaki?

00:10:16.951 --> 00:10:17.918 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh, my God!

00:10:17.952 --> 00:10:18.919 position:35% line:89% align:start
Takemichi!

00:10:18.953 --> 00:10:19.753 position:38% line:89% align:start
