-(victim gurgling)

00:14:51.091 --> 00:14:54.161 position:21% line:89% align:start
(gasps) That's Baji!

00:14:55.362 --> 00:14:57.064 position:30% line:89% align:start
Whoa, Kazutora!

00:14:57.097 --> 00:14:58.932 position:7% line:89% align:start
What the hell's going on here?

00:14:58.966 --> 00:14:59.967 position:33% line:89% align:start
What is this?

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:01.301 position:21% line:89% align:start
What's it look like?

00:15:01.335 --> 00:15:02.737 position:27% line:89% align:start
A test of faith.

00:15:02.771 --> 00:15:04.071 position:38% line:89% align:start
What for?

00:15:04.104 --> 00:15:07.207 position:19% line:83% align:start
To test Baji's
commitment to Valhalla.

00:15:07.241 --> 00:15:10.010 position:16% line:83% align:start
Going from Toman to us is
like changing religions.

00:15:10.043 --> 00:15:12.913 position:19% line:83% align:start
You have to prove to
us you really mean it.

00:15:12.946 --> 00:15:14.849 position:21% line:83% align:start
The guy Baji's
beating on right now

00:15:14.883 --> 00:15:17.384 position:19% line:83% align:start
is Toman's first
division vice captain.

00:15:17.418 --> 00:15:19.788 position:24% line:83% align:start
He was Baji's most
trusted lieutenant.

00:15:19.821 --> 00:15:21.756 position:21% line:83% align:start
The first division's
vice captain?!

00:15:21.790 --> 00:15:23.991 position:13% line:89% align:start
Toman is Valhalla's enemy.

00:15:25.959 --> 00:15:28.929 position:19% line:83% align:start
If he's going to betray
his former god Mikey,

00:15:28.962 --> 00:15:30.899 position:21% line:83% align:start
he's gotta stomp
out his old beliefs.

00:15:30.931 --> 00:15:35.936 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(Baji panting)
-(foreboding music)

00:15:41.676 --> 00:15:45.946 position:16% line:83% align:start
(exhales) Well, then, was
that good enough for you?

00:15:45.979 --> 00:15:47.549 position:27% line:89% align:start
What do you say?

00:15:47.582 --> 00:15:49.149 position:21% line:89% align:start
Am I in Valhalla now,

00:15:51.820 --> 00:15:56.390 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hanma?

00:15:57.659 --> 00:15:59.193 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Hanma chuckles)

00:15:59.226 --> 00:16:01.495 position:5% line:89% align:start
That was some brutal shit, dude.

00:16:01.529 --> 00:16:04.131 position:19% line:83% align:start
That guy's been by your
side, like, forever.

00:16:04.164 --> 00:16:06.333 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yeah, I'm surprised
you took it that far.

00:16:07.367 --> 00:16:08.803 position:27% line:89% align:start
(member exhales)

00:16:08.837 --> 00:16:10.404 position:38% line:89% align:start
Shut up.

00:16:10.437 --> 00:16:12.507 position:24% line:83% align:start
I don't care about
your opinions.

00:16:15.476 --> 00:16:17.444 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kazutora!

00:16:17.478 --> 00:16:18.445 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hey, boss.

00:16:19.681 --> 00:16:21.649 position:27% line:89% align:start
You all set now?

00:16:21.683 --> 00:16:22.817 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:16:22.851 --> 00:16:26.019 position:24% line:83% align:start
Let me present
Takemichi Hanagaki.

00:16:26.053 --> 00:16:27.454 position:5% line:89% align:start
He's the newest member of Toman.

00:16:27.488 --> 00:16:28.489 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh?!

00:16:30.324 --> 00:16:31.425 position:41% line:89% align:start
Oh, no!

00:16:31.458 --> 00:16:34.027 position:13% line:83% align:start
Don't tell me the next test
of faith victim is...?!

00:16:44.906 --> 00:16:46.406 position:21% line:89% align:start
So, you're Hanagaki?

00:16:48.442 --> 00:16:49.611 position:33% line:89% align:start
Step forward.

00:16:50.745 --> 00:16:54.381 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Go!
-(Takemichi grunts)

00:16:54.414 --> 00:16:56.083 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasps)

00:16:56.116 --> 00:16:58.318 position:24% line:89% align:start
You again. Dumbass.

00:16:58.352 --> 00:17:00.053 position:5% line:89% align:start
Did you come here to get killed?

00:17:01.121 --> 00:17:02.122 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Member] Kill him!

00:17:02.757 --> 00:17:03.725 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Members] Kill him!

00:17:03.758 --> 00:17:04.826 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:04.859 --> 00:17:05.760 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:05.793 --> 00:17:06.761 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:06.794 --> 00:17:07.695 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:07.729 --> 00:17:09.062 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:09.096 --> 00:17:10.798 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] I came
here to take Baji back,

00:17:10.832 --> 00:17:12.534 position:10% line:89% align:start
but now Baji's gonna kill me!

00:17:12.567 --> 00:17:13.333 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Members] Kill him!

00:17:13.367 --> 00:17:14.334 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:14.368 --> 00:17:15.335 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:15.369 --> 00:17:16.370 position:38% line:89% align:start
Kill him!

00:17:18.071 --> 00:17:20.340 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hanma] One of Toman's
founding members

00:17:20.374 --> 00:17:24.077 position:19% line:83% align:start
and its first division
captain, Keisuke Baji!

00:17:24.111 --> 00:17:27.147 position:21% line:83% align:start
He now says he wants
to leave Toman behind

00:17:27.180 --> 00:17:28.448 position:24% line:89% align:start
and join Valhalla.

00:17:28.482 --> 00:17:29.884 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Toman's fishy to me.
-(members murmuring)

00:17:29.918 --> 00:17:32.520 position:21% line:83% align:start
Is that a good thing
or a bad thing?

00:17:32.554 --> 00:17:33.521 position:24% line:89% align:start
A good thing, duh.

00:17:33.555 --> 00:17:35.389 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sounds too good
to be true to me.

00:17:35.422 --> 00:17:37.090 position:13% line:89% align:start
For those of you wondering,

00:17:37.124 --> 00:17:39.894 position:21% line:83% align:start
the fact is, this is
one hell of a deal.

00:17:39.928 --> 00:17:42.462 position:24% line:83% align:start
Having Baji here
will be a huge help

00:17:42.496 --> 00:17:44.464 position:21% line:83% align:start
in our plan to
finally crush Toman.

00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:48.002 position:19% line:83% align:start
But for right now,
there's still one thing

00:17:48.036 --> 00:17:50.605 position:24% line:83% align:start
that we need to be
absolutely sure of.

00:17:52.205 --> 00:17:56.310 position:13% line:83% align:start
Because for all we know, he
might just be a Toman spy!

00:17:56.343 --> 00:17:58.613 position:21% line:83% align:start
Which is why we took
the extra precaution

00:17:58.646 --> 00:18:01.649 position:24% line:83% align:start
of having Kazutora
bring us a witness.

00:18:01.683 --> 00:18:03.150 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasps)

00:18:03.183 --> 00:18:05.687 position:13% line:83% align:start
This court will now summon
the witness to testify!

00:18:09.791 --> 00:18:11.391 position:24% line:89% align:start
Takemichi Hanagaki.

00:18:11.425 --> 00:18:13.528 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh, uh, yes?

00:18:13.561 --> 00:18:16.430 position:16% line:83% align:start
Will you tell this
court exactly what words

00:18:16.463 --> 00:18:20.100 position:13% line:83% align:start
you heard Baji here say
at the last Toman meeting?

00:18:20.133 --> 00:18:21.134 position:38% line:89% align:start
Well, he,

00:18:22.235 --> 00:18:25.039 position:16% line:83% align:start
he said that he quit and
that from that day on,

00:18:25.073 --> 00:18:26.741 position:16% line:89% align:start
Toman would be his enemy.

00:18:28.943 --> 00:18:31.278 position:5% line:89% align:start
And Kazutora, what do you think?

00:18:31.311 --> 00:18:34.114 position:19% line:83% align:start
We did a test of faith
and we heard a witness.

00:18:34.147 --> 00:18:36.383 position:7% line:89% align:start
So I think that's good enough.

00:18:36.416 --> 00:18:38.920 position:5% line:89% align:start
Baji could be very useful to us.

00:18:38.953 --> 00:18:41.756 position:13% line:83% align:start
He knows what's new with
Toman since I've been gone.

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:45.492 position:21% line:83% align:start
He's definitely worth
having in Valhalla.

00:18:45.526 --> 00:18:46.326 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Hanma] Hmm.

00:18:47.829 --> 00:18:49.631 position:19% line:89% align:start
So are you sure, Baji?

00:18:49.664 --> 00:18:52.066 position:24% line:83% align:start
Because we're going
to crush Toman,

00:18:52.100 --> 00:18:54.669 position:7% line:89% align:start
and in the process, of course,

00:18:54.702 --> 00:18:56.638 position:21% line:89% align:start
Mikey's going to die.

00:18:56.671 --> 00:18:59.272 position:33% line:89% align:start
(gasps) Huh?

00:19:01.174 --> 00:19:02.175 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Baji] Yeah.

00:19:03.443 --> 00:19:05.312 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll help you do that, Kazutora.

00:19:07.115 --> 00:19:08.516 position:27% line:89% align:start
(Takemichi gasps)

00:19:08.549 --> 00:19:10.283 position:24% line:83% align:start
Well, then, I
think it's decided.

00:19:12.419 --> 00:19:13.420 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:19:13.453 --> 00:19:14.622 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah!

00:19:14.656 --> 00:19:16.223 position:19% line:89% align:start
Then from this day on,

00:19:16.256 --> 00:19:19.861 position:13% line:83% align:start
Keisuke Baji is officially
a member of Valhalla!

00:19:19.894 --> 00:19:22.764 position:24% line:89% align:start
(members cheering)

00:19:26.067 --> 00:19:28.536 position:30% line:89% align:start
(Hanma giggles)

00:19:28.569 --> 00:19:30.104 position:41% line:89% align:start
No way!

00:19:30.138 --> 00:19:31.572 position:27% line:89% align:start
If this happens,

00:19:31.606 --> 00:19:34.241 position:10% line:83% align:start
